<item>
            <title>[OAK-823] Missing validation for jcr:uuid property</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-823</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A jcr:uuid property (defined by mix:referenceable) is defined to be&lt;br/&gt;
an autocreated/mandatory/protected property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently the commit hooks don&apos;t make sure that in this case &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the value is a valid UUID (propertyAdded)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;nor does it assert that this property can never be modified (propertyChanged)&lt;br/&gt;
note however, that i might be removed in case the mixin type is removed or&lt;br/&gt;
the primary type gets modified and there is no valid definition left for&lt;br/&gt;
that property. since the type-validator must assert that the mandatory&lt;br/&gt;
property exists (if the node is referenceable) there is not extra verification&lt;br/&gt;
needed in the case of removal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
